                    <div class="section active" id="learning_intent">
                        <div class="section-header"><h3>LEARNING INTENT</h3></div>
                        <div class="section-content"><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div style="position: relative; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0;"><div class="key-definition-box"><h4>MODULE OVERVIEW</h4><div><p><b>Inclusive Leadership in Action: Inclusion, Bias & Shaping Culture</b></p><p>This module is designed for learners on the <b>Team Leader Level 3 Apprenticeship</b> who are developing the knowledge, skills, and behaviours needed to lead diverse teams effectively and foster inclusive workplace environments.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="text-content-render"><p><b>Who is this module for?</b></p><p>This module is for Team Leader Level 3 apprentices who are building their capability to lead with inclusion at the forefront. Whether you are new to leadership or looking to strengthen your understanding of diversity, equity, and inclusion (DEI), this module will provide you with practical tools and insights to apply in your day-to-day role.</p></div></div><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="text-content-render"><p><b>How does this link to prior learning?</b></p><p>This module builds directly on your learning from <b>Leading People – Month 3: Team Culture & DEI / Inclusion & Compliance</b>. In that session, you explored the foundations of team culture, the importance of diversity and inclusion, and compliance requirements related to equality legislation. This module takes those concepts further by focusing on how you, as a team leader, can actively shape an inclusive culture and address unconscious bias in your leadership practice.</p></div></div><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="text-content-render"><p><b>How does this link to the live training session?</b></p><p>This online module serves as essential <b>pre-work</b> to prepare you for your upcoming live workshop. By completing this module before the session, you will:</p><ul><li>Arrive with a shared understanding of key DEI concepts and terminology</li><li>Be ready to engage in meaningful discussions and activities</li><li>Have reflected on your own experiences and potential biases</li><li>Be prepared to apply learning to real workplace scenarios during the workshop</li></ul></div></div><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="text-content-render"><p><b>What will you gain from completing the pre-work and post-work?</b></p><p><b>Pre-work (this module):</b></p><ul><li>A solid foundation in DEI principles and inclusive leadership</li><li>Awareness of unconscious bias and its impact on decision-making</li><li>Practical strategies you can begin applying immediately</li><li>Preparation for active participation in your live session</li></ul><p><b>Post-work (following the live session):</b></p><ul><li>Opportunities to consolidate your learning through reflection activities</li><li>SMART goal setting to embed inclusive practices into your leadership approach</li><li>Evidence of off-the-job learning for your apprenticeship portfolio</li><li>Continued development resources to support your growth as an inclusive leader</li></ul></div></div></div>
