                    <div class="section" id="reflection">
                        <div class="section-header"><h3>REFLECTION</h3></div>
                        <div class="section-content"><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div style="position: relative; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0;"><div class="key-definition-box"><h4>1-MINUTE REFLECTION</h4><div><p>Take a moment to reflect on what you have learned about Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion.</p><p>Think about your own workplace – your team, your department, or your organisation as a whole.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="feedback-box-render"><h4>Consider these questions:</h4><p><b>Which of the three – Diversity, Equity, or Inclusion – do you see MOST in your workplace?</b></p><p>Think about:</p><ul><li>Is there a good mix of different people? (Diversity)</li><li>Do people get the support they need to succeed? (Equity)</li><li>Do people feel they belong and that their voice matters? (Inclusion)</li></ul><textarea placeholder="Write your thoughts here... Which element do you see most strongly in your workplace, and what evidence do you see of it?"></textarea></div></div><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="feedback-box-render"><h4>Now consider:</h4><p><b>Which of the three – Diversity, Equity, or Inclusion – do you see LEAST in your workplace?</b></p><p>Think about:</p><ul><li>Where might there be gaps or room for improvement?</li><li>What barriers might exist that prevent people from participating fully?</li><li>What small changes could make a difference?</li></ul><textarea placeholder="Write your thoughts here... Which element do you see least in your workplace? What opportunities might exist to strengthen this area?"></textarea></div></div><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="text-content-render"><p><b>Keep these reflections in mind:</b></p><p>There are no right or wrong answers here. The purpose of this reflection is to help you start noticing DEI in your everyday work environment.</p><p>As you continue through this module and into your live workshop, you will build on these observations and develop practical strategies for strengthening DEI in your team.</p><p><b>Well done on completing this introduction to DEI!</b></p><p>You now have a foundation in the key concepts of Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion. In the next sections of this module, you will explore unconscious bias and practical inclusive leadership behaviours.</p></div></div></div>
